---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro'
---

<ProjectLayout
  badge="IEEE Research · BDAI 2026 · Accepted"
  title="Edge AI Fault Detection — Induction Motors at 99.3% Accuracy."
  description="A lightweight CNN-LSTM model that detects induction motor faults at the edge with 99.3% accuracy, consuming 10× less energy than server-side inference — accepted to IEEE BDAI 2026."
  coverImage="/portfolio/images/cover_bdai.webp"
  coverAlt="Edge AI fault detection system for induction motors"
  ogImage="https://alesso-24.github.io/portfolio/images/cover_bdai.webp"
  meta={[
    { label: 'Venue',     value: 'IEEE BDAI 2026 — Big Data & AI' },
    { label: 'Status',    value: '✓ Accepted · IEEE Xplore ~Sep 2026' },
    { label: 'Accuracy',  value: '99.3% (test set)' },
    { label: 'Stack',     value: 'Python · TensorFlow Lite · ESP32' },
    { label: 'Role',      value: 'Lead Researcher & Implementation' },
  ]}
>

  <!-- IEEE coming soon badge -->
  <div data-reveal style="margin: clamp(20px,3vh,32px) 0 0; display:flex; align-items:center; gap:16px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <div style="
      display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:10px;
      padding:12px 24px; border-radius:100px;
      background:rgba(37,64,192,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(37,64,192,0.2);
    ">
      <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="#2540c0" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5zM2 17l10 5 10-5M2 12l10 5 10-5"/></svg>
      <span style="font:700 12px 'Hanken Grotesk',system-ui,sans-serif; letter-spacing:0.12em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#2540c0;">
        IEEE Xplore · Expected September 2026
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- Pull quote -->
  <blockquote class="pull-quote" data-reveal>
    <p>"The industrial floor can't wait for the cloud. We pushed a full fault-detection brain to a microcontroller — and it works better than expected."</p>
  </blockquote>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>The Industrial Problem.</h2>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    Induction motors power roughly 70% of global industrial electricity consumption.
    When one fails unexpectedly, downtime costs can reach tens of thousands of dollars
    per hour in a production environment. Traditional condition monitoring sends vibration
    and current data to a server for analysis — introducing latency and cloud dependency
    that makes real-time intervention impossible.
  </p>
  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100">
    We asked: can a micro-controller at the motor itself detect faults as accurately as
    a remote server — and do it an order of magnitude more efficiently?
    The answer informed this entire research trajectory.
  </p>

  <!-- Stats -->
  <div class="stat-highlight" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="140">
    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:clamp(16px,3vw,40px);">
      {[
        { num: '99.3%', label: 'Classification accuracy on test set' },
        { num: '10×', label: 'Lower energy vs. server-side inference' },
        { num: '4', label: 'Fault classes detected (incl. healthy)' },
      ].map(({ num, label }) => (
        <div style="border-top: 2px solid #2540c0; padding-top: 16px;">
          <div data-counter={num} style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif; font-size:clamp(28px,3.5vw,52px); color:#2540c0; line-height:1; margin-bottom:8px;">{num}</div>
          <p style="margin:0; font-size:13px; color:#6f6a5f; letter-spacing:0.04em;">{label}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h2 class="section-h2" data-reveal>Model Architecture & Approach.</h2>

  <p class="prose" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="60">
    The model combines a 1D CNN for spatial feature extraction from motor current signatures,
    stacked with LSTM layers to capture temporal dependencies in the bearing fault progression.
    The full pipeline was quantized to INT8 using TensorFlow Lite, enabling deployment on
    an ESP32 microcontroller with less than 512KB of RAM.
  </p>

  <div class="tech-grid" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="100">
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">01</div>
      <h3>Signal Preprocessing</h3>
      <p>Motor stator current signals processed through windowed FFT and time-domain
      feature extraction — building structured input tensors from raw ADC readings.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">02</div>
      <h3>CNN-LSTM Fusion</h3>
      <p>Convolutional filters detect fault-frequency signatures; LSTM layers track
      fault progression over time — achieving cloud-level accuracy at edge-level cost.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <div class="tech-num">03</div>
      <h3>TFLite INT8 Quantization</h3>
      <p>Post-training quantization reduces the model from float32 to INT8 — 4× smaller,
      runs on microcontrollers with virtually no accuracy penalty (≤0.2%).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Figures -->
  <div data-reveal style="border-radius:18px; overflow:hidden; margin: clamp(28px,4vh,48px) 0; box-shadow: 0 22px 50px -24px rgba(37,64,192,0.35);">
    <img src="/portfolio/images/paper1.webp" alt="CNN-LSTM architecture for fault detection"
         loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%; height:auto; display:block;" />
  </div>

  <div data-reveal style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:clamp(12px,2vw,24px); margin-bottom: clamp(28px,4vh,48px);">
    <div style="border-radius:14px; overflow:hidden; box-shadow:0 18px 44px -20px rgba(37,64,192,0.3);">
      <img src="/portfolio/images/paper3.webp" alt="Latency comparison: edge vs. server"
           loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%; height:auto; display:block;" />
    </div>
    <div style="border-radius:14px; overflow:hidden; box-shadow:0 18px 44px -20px rgba(234,106,46,0.3);">
      <img src="/portfolio/images/paper5.webp" alt="PCA visualization of fault classes"
           loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="width:100%; height:auto; display:block;" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout" data-reveal>
    <strong>Edge vs. Cloud Energy Cost.</strong>
    A single fault-detection inference on the server costs ~110mJ per query (including network
    round-trip). On the ESP32 with INT8 TFLite: ~11mJ. At 1 inference/second over an 8-hour
    shift, that's the difference between 3.2Wh and 317Wh per motor — compounding at factory scale.
  </div>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  .pull-quote {
    border-left: 3px solid #2540c0;
    margin: clamp(32px,5vh,56px) 0;
    padding: clamp(16px,2.5vw,24px) clamp(20px,3vw,32px);
    background: #efe7d8;
    border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
  }
  .pull-quote p {
    margin: 0; font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    font-size: clamp(17px, 1.9vw, 24px); line-height: 1.4;
    color: #211f1a; font-style: italic;
  }
  .tech-num {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif; font-size: 32px;
    color: #2540c0; line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 12px; letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
</style>
